text: Ann Mitchell (born 22 April 1939) is a British actress. She was born in London. She became known in the 1980s when she starred as Dolly Rawlins in the crime series Widows as well as the sequels Widows 2 and She's Out. In 2011, she was cast as Cora Cross in the BBC soap opera EastEnders. She also starred as Mrs. Warren in Mrs. Warren's Profession and her Laurence Olivier Award nominated performance in Through the Leaves. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1939 births Category:Living people Category:British movie actors Category:British television actors Category:British stage actors Category:British voice actors Category:Actors from London
